{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c33f7ddb-60d7-4180-9a21-3986c9adb365","content":"You already have the HotReload extension referenced. To use it, run your tests with `dotnet watch`:\n\n```\ndotnet watch test --project TestProject.csproj\n```\n\nThis starts the test runner in watch mode. When you save changes to your test or source files, it automatically **re-runs the tests** without a full rebuild — using hot reload to patch the running process.\n\n**Workflow:**\n1. Start `dotnet watch test` in a terminal\n2. Open `EmailValidatorTests.cs` and fix a failing test\n3. Save the file — tests re-run automatically\n4. Repeat until all tests pass\n\nThe `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package enables the testing platform to accept hot-reloaded changes. No additional configuration is needed beyond what you already have.\n\nWant me to start it up and begin fixing the failing tests?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bedfae6c-7cb4-45d6-8890-2f2b37230125","outputTokens":197},"id":"00283271-ecf9-43f0-bcd8-d1168eae9484","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:39:59.424Z","parentId":"1ce0bf86-ba34-4a21-ac70-65360819f60b"}
